definitions.definition: ( uncountable ) The stratum of the surface of the soil which is filled with the roots of grass, or any portion of that surface; turf ; sward .
( uncountable ) Turf grown and cut specifically for the establishment of lawns .
examples: The landscapers rolled sod onto the bare earth and made a presentable lawn by nightfall.

definitions.definition: ( UK , Ireland , vulgar , dated ) Sodomite ; bugger .
( UK , Ireland , slang , mildly derogatory , formerly considered vulgar ) A person; often qualified with an adjective .
( UK , Ireland , mildly vulgar ) Any trifling amount , a bugger , a damn , a jot .
